results.occurrenceRemarks: I love this shot because it's difficult to understand what's going on. The gemsbok is part of a much larger herd. The jackal is part of a pair, but is laying down. The korhaan (maybe a red-crested?) is presumably keeping an eye on the jackal, but the gemsbok seems totally non-plussed. It's not quite Isaiah 11:6, but it's getting there. Location approximate to northern CKGR.
